channel.title: What am I doing wrong
channel.description:
I have my own server and have been trying to been making it no-ip for ages, I tried everything I looked at God of Ikiliki's Private server guide and still no luck. I followed the guide step by step, I really do not know what I am doing wrong. I have McAfee Security Program on my computer, does that have anything to do with it?
I am really lost. -------------------
God of Ikiliki I know you were busy the last time I asked you, but if you come, can you explain?
------ By the way I am using a belkin router...

item.title: What am I doing wrong
item.dc:creator: @njr99 njr99
item.description:
@njr99 wrote:

first you might need to portforward so…
go to your firewall setting and go to exeptions…add port
name:rsps
port:(your port ex. 43594)

and for the no-ip thing you need to go to the download tab at no-ip.com after you created account. then download it, install it, then open it(bottom right hand side of your screen) then click where it says click here to create host,make a host and use no-ip or(suggesting that)change nothing but the host name
